items.name: Azure Shark Filet
items.description: A filet from a fish from the ocean. Could be used to make food.

items.name: Azure Shark Products
items.description: Filets of fish from an Ocean Fish. Can also provide Fish Oil or Scales.

items.name: Azure Shark Scale
items.description: A fish scale crystalized by the salt in the ocean. Svim would be interested in this.

items.name: Baffled Adventurer's Note
items.description: A piece of parchment with some writing on it.

items.name: Basic Amber Resin
items.description: Pure Resin from a tree. Could be used to make wood polish.

items.name: Basic Bait
items.description: Bait made at a fishing station. Could be used to catch larger fish.

items.name: Basic Bait and Shells
items.description: Materials from a fish processed at a fishing station. Contains some amount of bait and shells.

items.name: Basic Berry
items.description: A juicy edible berry. Probably better cooked.

items.name: Basic Building Elixir
items.description: An elixir made by a scholar. Increases your building speed. Does not stack with other elixirs.

items.name: Basic Chemical Catalyst
items.description: A catalyst that can be made and used by scholars to create various potions or consumables.

items.name: Basic Chum
items.description: Can be used to chum fishing nodes in the ocean. Once chummed, nodes remain fishable for 15 minutes.

items.name: Basic Citric Berry
items.description: A berry full of citric acid. Could be used by a scholar to make a solvent for refining metal.

items.name: Basic Clay Lump
items.description: A lump of clay. Could be used to build or craft something, or even pave the ground.

items.name: Basic Crafting Elixir
items.description: An elixir made by a scholar. Increases your crafting speed. Does not stack with other elixirs.

items.name: Basic Crop Oil
items.description: Oil made from mashing starbulbs. Could be used to make wood treatment at a scholar station.

items.name: Basic Embergrain
items.description: Embergrains which could be cooked into dough.

items.name: Basic Embergrain Dough
items.description: A dough ball made of Embergrain Flour.

items.name: Basic Embergrain Flour
items.description: A pile of Embergrain Flour. Could be used to bake something.

items.name: Basic Embergrain Plant
items.description: Can be split into Embergrain to cook or Embergrain Seeds to replant.

items.name: Basic Embergrain Products
items.description: Food products and seeds husked from a plant.

items.name: Basic Embergrain Seeds
items.description: Can be grown into an Embergrain plant in a farming field.

items.name: Basic Fertilizer
items.description: A basic fertilizer made at a farming station. Used for fertilizing crops.

items.name: Basic Firesand
items.description: Various stones that have been boiled and baked by a cook. Can be used to refine bricks.

items.name: Basic Fish Oil
items.description: Oil made from fish. Can be used for making leather treatment and ink.

items.name: Basic Flower
items.description: A flower that could be grinded up to make pigment or used to make tea.

items.name: Basic Food Waste
items.description: Discarded scraps of food. Can be used to create fertilizer.

items.name: Basic Gathering Elixir
items.description: An elixir made by a scholar. Increases your gathering speed. Does not stack with other elixirs.

items.name: Basic Healing Potion
items.description: A potion made from Hexmoths. Increases one's ability to naturally recover from damages.

items.name: Basic Ink
items.description: Ink made of pigment and fish oil. Could be used by a scholar to transcribe stone carvings found in hieroglyphs around the world and in ruins.

items.name: Basic Leather Treatment
items.description: A treatment made by Scholars to purify leather further.

items.name: Basic Metal Solvent
items.description: A solvent used to purify metal further.

items.name: Basic Mortar
items.description: Mortar needed for crafting stone blocks and buildings. Can be made at a masonry station.

items.name: Basic Mushroom
items.description: A plump mushroom that looks edible and quite hearty. Probably better cooked.

items.name: Basic Pigment
items.description: Pigment made from flowers. Could be used for ink or certain clothing.

items.name: Basic Potter's Mix
items.description: A mix made by a mason that can be used to make various clay goods.

items.name: Basic Raw Meat
items.description: A piece of meat from a wild animal. Could be used as a cooking ingredient.

items.name: Basic Sand
items.description: Sand. Primarily used to make glass.

items.name: Basic Stamina Potion
items.description: A potion made by a scholar. Increases your active stamina regen, allowing you to regenerate stamina while taking other actions for a short time.

items.name: Basic Starbulb
items.description: A Starlight Onion. Maybe a cook could make something good out of this?

items.name: Basic Starbulb Plant
items.description: Can be husked into Starlight Onions to eat or Starlight Onion Seeds to replant.

items.name: Basic Starbulb Products
items.description: Food products and seeds husked from a plant.

items.name: Basic Starbulb Seeds
items.description: Can be grown into a Starlight Onion Plant in a farming field.

items.name: Basic Tannin
items.description: A material made from processing water and bark in a tanning tub. Used to tan leather.

items.name: Basic Wispweave Plant
items.description: Can be split into Wispweave Filament for tailoring and Wispweave Seeds to replant.

items.name: Basic Wispweave Products
items.description: Filaments and other cloth products husked from a wispweave plant.

items.name: Basic Wispweave Seeds
items.description: Can be grown into a Wispweave Plant in a farming field. Produces filaments used for making cloth.

items.name: Basic Wood Polish
items.description: Polish that can be used to enhance wood planks. Made by a scholar from Resin and Crop Oil.

items.name: Beanie Present Output
items.description: Contains a random colored beanie.

items.name: Beech Seed
items.description: A seed to plant a sapling in a tree pot.

items.description: Research notes about advanced cloth materials.

items.name: Beginner's Leather Research
items.description: Research notes about advanced leather materials.

items.name: Beginner's Metal Research
items.description: Research notes about advanced metal materials.

items.name: Beginner's Stone Research
items.description: Research notes about advanced stone materials.

items.name: Beginner's Wood Research
items.description: Research notes about advanced wood materials.

items.description: A seed to plant a sapling in a tree pot.
